    "hadith_number": "3580",
    "english_translation": "Narrated: Malik ibn Abdullah saw a companion walking and leading his horse at Dhat al-Jawn. He called to him: O brother, why don't you ride? He replied: I heard the Messenger of Allah ﷺ say: Whoever has dusty feet in the way of Allah, Mighty and Exalted, Paradise will be obligatory for him. So I want that to be obligatory for me from my Lord, and let my beast be returned to me. Let it enrich me from my companion's beast. Malik said: Allah is Greatest! Then he dismounted and the people dismounted with him, all together, and they led their beasts. Ibn Ayyash said: The one who was walking was Iyad ibn Ghunam.",
