    "hadith_number": "3582",
    "english_translation": "Narrated by Al-Hakam ibn Minaa: The Prophet ﷺ said to Umar: Gather for me from the Quraysh who are here. Umar asked: O Messenger of Allah, shall you go out to them or shall they enter to you? The Prophet ﷺ said: I will go out to them. So he went out and said: O assembly of Quraysh, is there anyone among you other than yourselves? They replied: No, except the children of our sisters. The Prophet ﷺ said: The child of the sister of the people is from them. Then he said: O assembly of Quraysh, know that the closest of people to me are the God-fearing. Take care that people do not come to you on the Day of Resurrection with deeds while you come carrying this world that you are bearing. So I will turn my face away from you. Then he recited: Indeed, the closest of the people to Abraham are those who followed him and this Prophet and those who have believed. And Allah is the Guardian of the believers (Al-Imran 68).",
